In [[cryptography]], '''F-FCSR''' is a [[stream cipher]] developed by Thierry Berger, François Arnault, and Cédric Lauradoux.   The core of the cipher is a [[Feedback with Carry Shift Registers|Feedback with Carry Shift Register]] (FCSR) automaton, which is similar to a [[LFSR]], but they perform operations with carries so their transition function is nonlinear.

F-FCSR was one of the eight algorithms selected for the [[eCRYPT]] network's [[eSTREAM]] Portfolio, but it was later removed because further analysis showed weaknesses.<ref>{{cite conference |url=https://www.iacr.org/archive/asiacrypt2008/53500563/53500563.pdf |title=Breaking the F-FCSR-H stream cipher in Real Time |last1=Hell |first1=Martin |last2=Johansson |first2=Thomas |editor=Pieprzyk, Josef |year=2008 |publisher=Springer Berlin / Heidelberg |booktitle=Lecture Notes in Computer Science |volume=5350 |conference=ASIACRYPT 2008 |pages=557–569 |doi=10.1007/978-3-540-89255-7_34 }}</ref>

